RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUNNING WATER was bumped at the break and forced inward some, responded to urging to gain the lead and the inside, lengthened command leaving the bend, received brief urging midstretch and proved much the best ridden out. MOCOWBELL broke well but soon was chasing RUNNING WATER from just outside, could not stay with that one leaving the turn, floated out some entering the lane and closed the gap some as the leader was allowed to coast in the waning yards. NATIONS DREAM broke inward, bumping RUNNING WATER, chased running widest and could only make up some ground deep stretch. TOO MUCH TUESDAY broke well but soon dropped to the back, angled out on the bend, came into the stretch behind NATIONS DREAM and had no late bid. DANCIN' MOLLY was a step slow then forced in at the start, chased from outside, angled in on the turn and had little to offer for the stretch run.

ENTRY.NAME: Too Much Tuesday
ENTRY.OWNER: Offspring Farm and Gavilsky II Lawrence J
ENTRY.COMMENT: angled out turn, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Dancin' Molly
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced in start, angled in turn, no late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Running Water
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, sent to lead, saved ground, ridden out

ENTRY.NAME: Nations Dream
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke inward, bumped, 3-4 path turn, best of rest

ENTRY.NAME: Mocowbell
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path, held 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEVIL'S RULE was kept close and taken inside, split rivals two wide as he commenced his bid on the bend, brushed with PEACOCK MAN upper stretch, took the rail with a furlong to go, soon gained the lead and kept the latter at bay under steady handling. PEACOCK MAN forwardly place from outside, progressed four wide on the turn, angled in some leaving the turn, brushed with DEVIL'S RULE upper stretch ad he vied for the lead, angled out some, had the advantage with a furlong to go but did not have enough left in the waning yards. PACHI in contention early, saved ground taking the bend, angled out midstretch and gained third inside the final sixteenth. STEPPIN SHEP prompted the pace between rivals on the backstretch, was three to four wide through the turn, began to fade in the lane, was forced out some by PACHI midstretch then continued to yield. GREAT PLAINES displayed early speed just off or along the rail for a half mile then gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Great Plaines
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, gave way inside stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Pachi
ENTRY.COMMENT: passed between tired ones

ENTRY.NAME: Devil's Rule
ENTRY.COMMENT: kept close inside, split foes 2 wide turn, led inside 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Steppin Shep
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-4 path turn, gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Peacock Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4 wide turn, 3 wide into stretch, vied, not enough left

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: R H SMOAKEM waited for room just off the inside on the backstretch, gained the rail on the bend, rallied leaving the turn, soon had a clear lead, drifted out some under left-handed pressure in the waning yards but kept STOSH at bay. STOSH well placed between rivals, advanced three wide on the turn, fanned out further for the drive and rallied belatedly deep stretch. READTHETRANSCRIPT vied for the early lead from inside, did not stay with MADE TO FIT into the bend, came off the rail some as he retreated between rivals on the turn, came two wide into the stretch and also found best stride too late. MADE TO FIT shared the early lead from outside, moved clear into turn, stayed just off the rail, floated out some entering the stretch, was no match for R H SMOAKEM and gradually wore down inside the last furlong. CARL G a step slow at the break, was hustled along early, went for the lead widest on the bend but could not sustain his bid through the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Readthetranscript
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed,retreated 2 wide turn, ame again 2 wide deep stretch

ENTRY.NAME: R H Smoakem
ENTRY.COMMENT: kept close, rail bid leaving turn, driven clear stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Stosh
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-4 wide, closing

ENTRY.NAME: Carl G
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4-5 wide turn, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Made to Fit
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside speed, 2-3 path turn, weakened stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 8 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IT'S BELLAMY TIME was quickly clear, showed the way from inside in hand, was challenged on the backstretch, roused with two furlongs to go, floated out to path three as he drew away from the rest again, began to wear down in the waning yards but held sway under steady handling. PRINCE OF MAYHEM prominent just outside IT'S BELLAMY TIME, angled outside CAMPAIGN SPY when that one took his path midway on the backstretch, was three wide on the second turn, lost ground staying outside CAMPAIGN SPY entering the lane, lugged in some upper stretch, brushing the latter, rallied the last eighth, came up short but was easily second best. CAMPAIGN SPY advanced three wide on the backstretch to vie for the lead outside IT'S BELLAMY TIME, began to yield leaving the second bend, stayed outside the latter into the lane, was crowded and altered in some upper stretch, continued to gradually fade but was unchallenged for third. SHOBIZ STAR soon trailed, ran widest of all and had little left for the stretch run.

ENTRY.NAME: Campaign Spy
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 2-4 path 2nd turn, gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: It's Bellamy Time
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace in hand, roused 1/4, drew off, weakened late, held on

ENTRY.NAME: Shobiz Star
ENTRY.COMMENT: wide trip, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Prince of Mayhem
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-5 path 2nd turn, brushed upper stretch, closing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 33. Maiden Claiming Purse 8000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ENVEY N ICE without early speed, picked up her pace after a quarter mile, split rivals two wide on the bend, fanned outside TINA'S TAPIZAR for the drive and swept past DESTINY'S DREAM inside the final sixteenth. DESTINY'S DREAM was hustled to contest the pace from just off the inside, gained the rail into the turn, jostled repeatedly inside TINA'S TAPIZAR as she slowly edged ahead in the stretch but did not have enough left the last sixteenth. BRIANA HARPER also without early speed while running widest, came into contention three wide on the bend, fanned out some for the stretch run, rallied belatedly but caught TINA'S TAPIZAR for third late. TINA'S TAPIZAR was also urged early to dispute the pace outside DESTINY'S DREAM, jostled repeatedly with that one in the lane then slowly yielded the with a sixteenth left. HARPER BRIANA raced closest to the pacesetters on the backstretch but bolted through the bend and had little to offer along the outside fence in the stretch. HURRYUPANDBYE failed to menace in a ground-saving trip.

ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, no factor

ENTRY.OWNER: Cox John E and Pohl Dennis

ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 wide turn, led inside 1/16, drawing off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 8 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500 (Claiming Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: U S HONOUR NAP stalked the leaders from outside on the backstretch, stayed in path three through the bend, rallied under urging in the lane, floated out slightly as he took the lead with a sixteenth left, held a straight path in the late going and was drawing off. BRIANS WAY hustled between horses early, was two wide on the turn, fanned out behind U S HONOUR NAP entering the stretch, angled outside the latter soon after, drifted out to path five, rallied inside the final eighth, lugged in under right-handed urging with a sixteenth to go, was steadied behind U S HONOUR NAP then drew clear for second the last seventy yards. LAGRUE shared the lead from outside from the beginning, was two wide through the bend, moved clear upper stretch but did not have enough left the last furlong. KEEN RESPONSE hesitated then broke inward, chased from outside, was also two wide on the turn, angled out to path four upper stretch and made up minor ground in the late going. TOWN CRIER displayed early speed from inside but flattened out for the drive. THACKER FROMM void of speed, though urged along, saved ground taking the turn, came off the rail for the stretch run and lacked a significant response. The rider of BRIANS WAY lodged an objection alleging interference from U S HONOUR NAP deep stretch. After their review, the stewards did not uphold that claim of foul.

ENTRY.NAME: Thacker Fromm
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Town Crier
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, flattened out stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Brians Way
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path turn, angled out upper stretch, lugged in 1/16, steadied

ENTRY.NAME: Keen Response
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated, broke inward, 2-3 path turn, mild gain late

ENTRY.NAME: U S Honour Nap
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked outside, 3 wide turn, got lead 1/16, drawing off

ENTRY.NAME: Lagrue
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside speed, 2 wide turn, drew clear, weakened last 1/8

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming Races For $3,200 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEIRUT BEAUTY jostled with KIANA'S LOVE several times while in close quarters leaving the chute, was just off the rail on the bend, lost some ground staying outside LIFE OF SATURDAYS entering the lane, was caught in a narrow path again upper stretch, leaned on KIANA'S LOVE as they approached the furlong marker, engaged LIFE OF SATURDAYS with a sixteenth left, was all out and slowly edged ahead. LIFE OF SATURDAYS edged ahead for the lead after the first sixteenth, moved clear and took the rail into the turn, drifted out to path three into the stretch, did not have enough left inside the final furlong but was clearly second best. KIANA'S LOVE jostled several times with BEIRUT BEAUTY while in close quarters leaving the chute, was steadied for nearly a sixteenth of a mile while in traffic midway on the backstretch, advanced four wide on the bend, lost further ground fanning outside BEIRUT BEAUTY entering the lane, was crowded by the latter upper stretch, altered out some with a furlong to go, was no match for the top pair in the late going but was unchallenged for third. WITCHING in contention early from inside, failed to keep up on the turn, came again upper stretch but could not sustain her bid the last eighth. TWO MORE TIMES chased from paths two or three, closed the gap some upper stretch then leveled off in the late going. BAILESTON LASSIE prominent from outside on the backstretch, faded three wide on the bend.

ENTRY.NAME: Witching
ENTRY.COMMENT: rail bid, hung

ENTRY.NAME: Two More Times
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Beirut Beauty
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-4 path turn, brushed upper stretch, edged ahead late

ENTRY.NAME: Kiana's Love
ENTRY.COMMENT: steadied in traffic early,3-5 path turn, brushed stretch,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Life of Saturdays
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed between, inside turn, floated into stretch, not enough left

ENTRY.NAME: Baileston Lassie
